        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Literature value. Data from the US Energy Information Administration for 2012, which provides data on net electricity production in each US State with various energy sources. Data from the States were aggregated on the level of US NERC regions. Data were given for the electricity production with total natural gas. This total production is split to production in electricity/CHP plants with a simple or combined cycle. This split is made based on information for total US (not specific to this NERC region) in the IEA electricity information (amount of electricity produced in electricity only and CHP plants) and information on installed electrical capacity with natural gas in the WEPP database. 

EIA. 2014. Statistics on electricity - Electricity data browser. Generation and thermal output. Net generation for electric power, annual.  U.S. Energy Information Administration; Independent Statistics&amp;Analysis.
IEA. 2014. Electricity Information 2014. ISBN 978-92-64-21692-1. International Energy Agency (IEA), Paris Cedex (FR).
WEPP 2014. World Electric Power Plants Database. PLATTS McGraw Hill Financial. http://www.platts.com/products/world-electric-power-plants-database</productionVolumeComment>
