      <elementaryExchange id="e4e7f136-8920-5215-b814-a031fc083012" unitId="de5b3c87-0e35-4fb0-9765-4f3ba34c99e5" variableName="water_cooling_UNO_input" casNumber="007732-18-5" amount="0.0504832" isCalculatedAmount="false" sourceId="eca6929a-3a96-41cb-b34a-d716ceed6492" sourceYear="2011" sourceFirstAuthor="Scown, C.D., et al." elementaryExchangeId="fc1c42ce-a759-49fa-b987-f1ec5e503db1" formula="H2O">
        <name xml:lang="en">Water, cooling, unspecified natural origin</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature (Scown, C.D., et al., 2011, Water Footprint of U.S. Trasportation Fuels;Scown, C.D., et al., 2011, Water Footprint of U.S. Trasportation Fuels (SI); Stiegel, 2008, Estimating Freshwater Needs to Meet Future Thermoelectric Generation Requirements; Floerke, M., 2009, Future changes of freshwater needs in the electricity production sector), (Vionnet, S., Quantis Water Database - Technical Report, 2012). Water use in this process is modelled based on literature (see references). The process boundaries are given by the boundaries of the power plant. The process ends when the energy (MJ) is produced and ready to be used for electricity production (kWh).
Calculated based on literature data.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
